page.title: 01THE D-BLOCK 0344 0321
page.content:
The {D-BLOCK}contains 2 pools ({MARTON and{FENEMERE}) it has most of { {MYDDLE, FENEMERE,MYDDLEWOOD}and{ {MERRINGTON GREEN}.There are four farms in it which are Alford farm, Lower Fenemere farm, Webscott farm and Castle farm. It has got a railway track going across one corner.
{MYDDLE }is in the North East corner of the {Block }and contains {LAUNCHBURYS} lorries,a{pub},a{Postoffice}and Alford and Castle farm( next to the Castle remains which is just the tower). Lower Fenemere farm is down{FENEMERE {ROAD}and Webscott farm is down{LOWER} {ROAD}.Most of the{D-BLOCK}is used for agriculture with only a few small villages.There is a Church in{MYDDLE which was built in {Saxon }times and rebuilt in 1744.
